pgTitle: List of Monuments of National Importance in Aurangabad circle

rows.text: Old tomb near Changiz Khan's palace
Temple of Shiva on the further side of the stream
Temple of Vishnu & Five Ghats at attached thereto.
Ancient sites and remains at Daimabad
Ancient site locally known as Ladmod
Dahihanda gate of outer city wall.
Khirki gate in the outer city wall
South -East bastion of the outer city wall together with 10 years of the adjacent wall on each side, variously known as panch Burj Hasrath Yab and containing a persion inscription.

Narnala Fort : i Akot Gateway, ii Ambar Mahal iii Delhi Gateway , iv Large & Two smaller Guns v Mahakali Gateway, vi Mendheao Gateway vii Shahapur Gateway, viii Sirpur Gateway ix Small Mosque, x Tank buikt to contain Oil & Ghee.
Tank in front of tomb of Lalkhan
City wall of Nawab Ismail Khan

Area containing the old remains of two temples consisting of a collection of Massive stones in two separate heaps, One immediately outside padampur to the north & the other immediately to the south of Ganeshpur
Remains of the temple to the North of the Village
Remains of the temple to the North-west of the village
Remains of the temple close to the south of the village Ganeshpur
All the remains of the circumambulation wall of Pauni Fort
Ancient mounds on which the modern temple of jagannath stands
Gaimukha Temple No 1 of Daitya Sudana
Square Kunda on the East of the Town
Dharmasala at North-East corner of the town
Temple of Vishnu, remains of an old building to the east of that temple and remains of small temple
Large high knoll immediately to the east of Bhandranath temple with remains of a temple, with huge stone carved blocks & a figure of Ganapati
Achaleshwar Temple & another small temple within an enclosure
Enclosure & buldings of the Gond Raja's Tomb just outside the Achaleshwar gate the city.

Lalpeth monoliths consisting of the sixteen colosal stone images. i. Anna Purna, ii. Bhim, iii. Fish, iv. Ganga v. Ganpati, vi. Hanuman, vii. Hanuman, viii. Kali, ix. Mahadev, x. Mahadev xi. Nandi, xii. Rawan, xiii. Snake, xiv. Tortoise xv. Ganpati xvi. Ganga
Mahadev Temple close to the Municipal office
Hemadpanthi Temple containing images of Dattatraya, Mahadev & Laxminarayan
Temple of the left side of shiva's Temple in Survey No. 418
Temple in front of the above in Survey No. 418
Temple between Durga's Temple and Math in Survey No. 141
Old gateways in the ruined fort & caves
Group of twenty cromlechs or Kistvaens
Ancient mound & monument known as Pawar's Gadhi
Old Temple of Siddheshwar with three inscriptions slabs
Remains of an old fort on the hill
Ancient Buddhist remains comprising monastery, stupas, Rock-cut inscription etc.
Remains of a very old shrines upon the western ride at the end of the Remtek hill consisting of a portion of porch of a temple and the mutilated image of Trivikram Avatara of Vishnu
Tank and Mandapa opposite to the Dattatraya's Temple
Hemadpanthi Temple of Shree Mahadev ( Taponeshwar )
